&lt;h1 class="relative group">What is the Reality
&lt;div id="what-is-the-reality" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#what-is-the-reality" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>You see something on a table and you ask yourself, &amp;ldquo;What is that?&amp;rdquo; &lt;br>
Answer: It looks like an apple, so it is an apple. &lt;br>
Then you ask, &amp;ldquo;How many apples are there?&amp;rdquo; &lt;br>
Answer: You know the counting, and after counting, you say it is three.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s a very simple process, isn&amp;rsquo;t it? &lt;br>
You know the truth after asking these two questions.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>The Way of Learning</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/the-way-of-learning/</link><pubDate>Mon, 19 Dec 2022 08:33:00 +0530</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/the-way-of-learning/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5208-The-Way-of-Learning.jpg" alt="The Way of Learning " />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">The Way of Learning
&lt;div id="the-way-of-learning" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#the-way-of-learning" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>If you want to teach your children the process of making tea &lt;br>
then you don&amp;rsquo;t force them to memorize s for sugar, &lt;br>
g for ginger, t for tea, w for water, m for milk, b for boil, etc. &lt;br>
And if they don&amp;rsquo;t memorize you punish them? &lt;br>
You don&amp;rsquo;t offer them tea? &lt;br>
You don&amp;rsquo;t allow them to come into the kitchen till they remember the complete vocabulary? &lt;br>
If this is your way of teaching then it is horrible, &lt;br>
Children don&amp;rsquo;t need any jail or hell &lt;br>
You are Yamraj and they are living in hell.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>